column2: we got all the ones they were offering. Shag (tempura fried roll)
column4: and the ham & eggs. I am biased... I love all things tempura fried so the shag was great for me. I'd never seen pieces of sushi done this way so it was a nice change of pace. The spicy tuna was surprisingly my favorite. Light and tasty. And then the ham & eggs.. You might wanna order this before ordering other rolls because its heavier since it has large pieces of meat in them. There's no egg in them
column5: the sauce on the side is supposed to be a play on the egg part of it. So if you're not big on raw fish this is probably for you.
